            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.17-18_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        22923 Allen Court
                        St. Clair Shores, Michigan
                        January 26, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It's been two years since I took your courses in the Writing of Poetry, The Critical Essay, and Epic America. Since that time, I've been in Detroit working as an advertising copy writer and, currently, as a drug salesman. More and more, however, I have been thinking that I should be happiest and most effective in a college teaching job.</p>
                
                <p>You see, I feel that I want to do something more important with my life -- and I believe teaching college students will be most satisfying. At least, I always got the impression that it was extremely satisfying to you. Consequently, I am applying to a number of universities to begin graduate work in English this fall, applying also for scholarships.</p>
                
                <p>In support of my scholarship applications I need letters of recommendation. I know it would help my cause immeasurably, if <hi rend="underline">you</hi> could find the time to write such a letter for me.</p>
                
                <p>Briefly, my background is this: I was Phi Beta Kappa, Phi Eta Sigma, in <hi rend="underline">Who's Who in American Colleges and Universities,</hi> edited both the weekly newspaper and the humor magazine. I took 36 hours of English, 21 of which were passed with a grade of <hi rend="caps">E</hi>, 12 of <hi rend="caps">S</hi>, and 3 of <hi rend="caps">M</hi>.</p>
                
                <p>I am enclosing the form that Michigan uses, along with a stamped, addressed envelope. I assume that similar information is required by Indiana and Iowa. I know, of course, Dr. Neihardt, that you are quite busy, but I shall be grateful if you can help me.</p>
                
                <p>The addresses:
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Graduate School</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Indiana University</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bloomington, Indiana</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dean of the Graduate College</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>State University of Iowa</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Iowa City, Iowa</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                
                <p>Thank you so much.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Joel J. Gold</signed>
                
                    <signed>Joel J. Gold</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
